'''Barqi Tojik''' is a national integrated power company of [[Tajikistan]]. The chairman of the company is Rustam Rahmatzoda.<ref name=neurope260910> {{Cite news |title=ADB grants $122 million grant to Tajikistan |newspaper=New Europe |url=http://www.neurope.eu/articles/ADB-grants-122-million-grant-to-Tajikistan/102931.php |date=2010-09-26 |accessdate=2010-11-13 }}{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} </ref><ref name=asiaplus281010> {{Cite news | title = Barqi Tojik: Electricity rationing will no be so strict this winter | first = Zarina | last = Ergasheva | publisher = ASIA-Plus | url = http://asiaplus.tj/en/news/31/70772.html | date = 2010-10-28 | accessdate = 2010-11-13}} </ref>
Barqi Tojik operates the [[Nurek Dam|Nurek Hydroelectric Power Plant]], the largest station in [[Central Asia]] with an installed generation capacity of 3 gigawatts (GW) and produces over 75% of Tajikistan’s electricity.<ref>{{cite news|title=Alstom Wins 500 kV Substation Project Using GIS Tech in Tajikistan|url=http://www.satrapia.com/news/article/alstom-wins-500-kv-substation-project-using-gis-tech-in-tajikistan/|accessdate=4 October 2012|newspaper=The Gazette of Central Asia|date=7 Feb 2012|publisher=Satrapia}}</ref>
