'''Men of the Trees''' is an international, non-profit, non-political, conservation organisation. It is involved in planting, maintenance and protection of trees. It was founded in [[Kenya]] on July 22, 1922, by [[Richard St. Barbe Baker]]. It was the precursor to another organisation also founded by St. Barbe Baker in 1924 as the '''[[International Tree Foundation]]''', in the [[United Kingdom]]. In 1929, a branch was opened in Palestine.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=CwA-AAAAIBAJ&sjid=gEkMAAAAIBAJ&pg=6347,2716036&dq=men-of-the-trees+palestine&hl=en The Men of the Trees], The [[Glasgow Herald]] - Jun 18, 1929.</ref>
There have been chapters in over 100 countries. By some estimates, organizations he founded or assisted have been responsible for planting at least 26 billion trees, internationally.<ref name=InJEnvStud1979>{{citation |year=1979 |title=26 trillion tree estimation |journal=The International Journal of Environmental Studies |volume=14 |page=77 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=n4deAAAAIAAJ&q=%2226+trillion+trees%22&dq=%2226+trillion+trees%22 |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref><ref name=Warre2006>{{citation |year=2006 |author=Warren, Piers |title=British Native Trees: Their Past and Present Uses |page=79 |place=UK |publisher=Wildeye |isbn=978-0-9541899-5-2 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=D95yQLOiP4MC&printsec=frontcover&dq=british+native+trees#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=14 August 2010}}</ref> In Australia there is currently still a small organization that goes by the name Men of the Trees,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.menofthetrees.com.au/about-mott/history/|title=Past & Present {{!}} Men Of The Trees WA|website=www.menofthetrees.com.au|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-13}}</ref> although in England, where the charity originated, the original charity has now been re-branded as the International Tree Foundation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://internationaltreefoundation.org/history/|title=History - International Tree Foundation|work=International Tree Foundation|access-date=2018-01-13|language=en-US}}</ref>
