'''Tulsi Gowda''' environmentalist from Honnali village, [[Ankola]] [[taluk]] in [[Karnataka]] state. She has planted 100,000 saplings and looks after the nurseries of the Forest department. Though she is an illiterate, she has made immense contributions towards preserving the environment. Her work has been honoured by the government and various organisations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tulsi Gowda to be felicitated|url=http://www.samachar.com/Snake-Marshal-and-Tulsi-Gowda-to-be-felicitated-lgccLQdadbi.html|publisher=Samachar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=‘Plant two saplings a year'|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/plant-two-saplings-a-year/article2080738.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|date=6 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= ‘Snake' Marshal and Tulsi Gowdato be felicitated |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/article2070134.ece?css=print |work=The Hindu|date=2 June 2011 }}</ref>

